{"id":"2012.14611","submitter":"Dakota Thor Ihli","authors":"Dakota Thor Ihli","title":"The structure of generic automorphisms of the random poset","comments":"38 pages, 8 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.LO math.CO math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We examine properties of generic automorphisms of the random poset, with the\ngoal of explicitly characterizing them. We associate to each automorphism an\nauxiliary first-order structure, consisting of the random poset equipped with\nan infinite sequence of binary relations which encode the action of the\nautomorphism. We then explicitly characterize generic automorphisms in terms of\nproperties of this structure. Two notable such properties are ultrahomogeneity,\nand universality for a certain class of finite structures in this language. As\nthis auxiliary structure seems to be new, we also address some model-theoretic\nquestions. In particular, this structure fails to be saturated, and its theory\nneither is $\\omega$-categorical nor admits quantifier-elimination, in contrast\nto many known ultrahomogeneous structures in finite languages. We also examine\norbitals -- order-convex hulls of orbits -- and their use in describing\nautomorphisms. In particular, we introduce and use new orders on the space of\norbitals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Dec 2020 05:18:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-01"}
