ity. Moreover, this work contributes\nto the development of ps-TALIF for determining absolute densities and quenching\ncoefficients of H and N atoms in plasmas. This is useful in numerous\nplasma-based applications (e.g. thin film synthesis, biomedical treatments,\nplasma-assisted combustion, ...), for which the knowledge of the\ndensity/kinetics of reactive atoms is essential.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Dec 2020 09:46:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-14"}
